Name: Sierra Nevada Pale Ale
Details: Sierra Nevada Pale Ale made hops famous, launching America’s craft beer movement with intense notes of citrus, pine, and smooth malt flavor. At 5.6% ABV, Sierra Nevada Pale Ale is still the gold standard for the American pale ale style, perfectly balancing bold hops and specialty caramel malt for easy drinkability. Using the now-iconic Cascade hop was a risky move when Sierra Nevada Pale Ale first came out. Cascade’s bold aromas of grapefruit and resinous pine shocked taste buds — then shot hoppy beers into the limelight.,Whether new to craft beer or a longtime fan, grab Sierra Nevada Pale Ale for its complex flavor and legendary hoppiness. This pack of beer is a crowd pleaser at happy hours, barbeques, and football watch parties. Sierra Nevada Pale Ale comes in cans, so load up the cooler for your next outdoor adventure (yup, the backyard counts). Sierra Nevada Brewing Co. is still 100% family owned, operated, and argued over.
